{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## What\n\nAdd **lease-based self-healing** on top of the C1 ref-lock primitive so a crashed pass-holder\nnever wedges the reconciler beyond one lease interval. Builds directly on C1.\n\n**Depends on: 524d-00fa-66ef-4432 (C1).** `renew()`, the blob schema (`heartbeat_ns`, `fence`), and\nthe CAS helpers are introduced by C1; this child extends that module — it is not standalone.\n\n- **Relative-duration, skew-proof lease (DynamoDB-lock-client pattern):** expiry is NOT a\n  cross-clone timestamp comparison. A contender records `(observed_oid, fence)`, waits one lease\n  interval measured on its **own** clock, re-reads; if `fence` and the ref oid are unchanged, the\n  holder made no progress for a full lease -> considered dead. This is why the stored `heartbeat_ns`\n  is only diagnostic and the design is skew-proof.\n- **`renew()`** (heartbeat) CAS-updates the blob's `heartbeat_ns` and **bumps `fence`** (`fence += 1`)\n  while the holder still owns the ref (old = observed oid). Its consumer is precisely the\n  progress-witness rule above.\n- **CAS-break-on-expiry:** a contender may steal **only** an expired lease, by CAS-replacing the blob\n  against the exact observed OID. Because the steal is a compare-and-swap on the observed oid, a\n  **double-break race resolves to exactly one winner** — the loser's CAS fails, it backs off and\n  does NOT also acquire.\n- **Lease + cadence config:** default lease **120 s**, heartbeat every **~lease/3**, read from a new\n  `[reconciler]` key `lock_lease_secs` (a constructor/param default, not a magic constant); the\n  heartbeat interval is derived from the lease, not independently hardcoded.\n- **`renew()` failure contract:** a rejected renewal CAS means the lease was lost/stolen. `renew()`\n  raises/returns a defined \"lease lost\" signal (it does NOT silently retry into another holder's\n  lock); the orchestrator (C3) turns that into a pass-abort.\n- Structured log emission for lease-steal, renewal-failure, and expiry-detection events.\n- Lives in `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/_ref_lock.py` (extends C1); no reconciler\n  orchestration wiring (that is C3). Extend the C1 ADR with the lease/heartbeat/fence contract.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `_ref_lock.py` gains `renew()` (owner-only CAS-update of `heartbeat_ns`, `fence += 1`) and a\n      lease-expiry evaluation that uses observed-no-progress-over-one-locally-measured-lease, not an\n      absolute cross-clone clock diff.\n- [ ] A contender CAS-breaks only an expired lease (no `fence`/oid progress across one lease); a live,\n      heartbeating holder is never stolen from (regression test).\n- [ ] Double-break race: two contenders race to steal one expired lock; exactly one wins, the other\n      observes CAS failure and does NOT acquire (single-winner regression test).\n- [ ] Lease duration + heartbeat cadence come from `[reconciler] lock_lease_secs` (default 120 s,\n      cadence ~lease/3), not hardcoded; `renew()` on CAS rejection raises a defined \"lease lost\"\n      signal rather than retrying.\n- [ ] Lease-steal / renewal-failure / expiry events emit structured logs. Non-integration suite green."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783219288436774001,"uuid":"5b9ffe74-a925-473a-b70c-2d9fa6dc15df"}